1
00:00:12,100 --> 00:00:13,967
[NOA] Every Filipino kid
knows it.

2
00:00:14,267 --> 00:00:16,200
-<i> You don't talk back.
</i>- [SOBS]

3
00:00:17,133 --> 00:00:19,267
<i>Nobody told me
that's how you trip</i>

4
00:00:19,267 --> 00:00:20,733
<i> for the rest of your life.</i>

5
00:00:21,500 --> 00:00:22,967
[WOMAN] Oh, dear.

6
00:00:23,267 --> 00:00:25,600
You still don't know
how to tie your own shoes?

7
00:00:28,700 --> 00:00:31,167
Are you expecting me
to do it for you?

8
00:00:33,333 --> 00:00:34,733
Answer me, Noa.

9
00:00:41,100 --> 00:00:43,733
Parents didn't teach
you any manners, huh?

10
00:00:43,733 --> 00:00:46,033
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC SWELLS]

11
00:00:46,033 --> 00:00:47,567
What did you say to her?!

12
00:00:47,567 --> 00:00:50,000
- I-I told-- [STAMMERS]
- Just what?!

13
00:00:50,567 --> 00:00:52,367
She'll be a nurse one day!

14
00:00:52,367 --> 00:00:54,600
And you, still bullying children

15
00:00:54,600 --> 00:00:57,100
with Dunkaroos frosting
on your fingers.

16
00:00:59,600 --> 00:01:01,033
[SIGHS]

17
00:01:03,033 --> 00:01:04,800
[GENTLE MUSIC PLAYING]

18
00:01:04,800 --> 00:01:07,067
[SOBS QUIETLY, SNIFFLES]

19
00:01:12,767 --> 00:01:14,333
Speak up for yourself.

20
00:01:14,833 --> 00:01:16,100
I can't.

21
00:01:17,200 --> 00:01:18,300
I know...

22
00:01:18,833 --> 00:01:21,600
I taught you
to listen to the elderly.

23
00:01:22,700 --> 00:01:24,400
But she's not old!

24
00:01:24,400 --> 00:01:26,333
She's still a child
with diabetes.

25
00:01:26,333 --> 00:01:33,333
[GENTLE MUSIC CONTINUES]

26
00:01:39,200 --> 00:01:40,200
[SQUEAKS]

27
00:01:40,767 --> 00:01:42,267
What are you? Seven?

28
00:01:42,767 --> 00:01:45,300
Tess didn't teach you
how to tie your shoe?

29
00:01:49,233 --> 00:01:50,200
Tess?

30
00:01:50,600 --> 00:01:51,700
I'm just kidding.

31
00:01:52,267 --> 00:01:54,100
Uh, don't haunt me.
[CHUCKLES WRYLY]

32
00:01:54,100 --> 00:01:55,400
I'm just kidding.

33
00:01:56,133 --> 00:02:00,467
[UPBEAT MUSIC PLAYING]

34
00:02:01,167 --> 00:02:02,267
"Tongue Tied"

35
00:02:04,167 --> 00:02:05,000
[NOA] Good morning!

36
00:02:05,000 --> 00:02:07,300
I brought donuts.
Please, take two.

37
00:02:07,300 --> 00:02:08,233
It's that kind of day.
[CHUCKLES]

38
00:02:08,233 --> 00:02:10,433
Oh, that's really
sweet of you. Thanks.

39
00:02:10,433 --> 00:02:11,833
Yes! Donuts!

40
00:02:12,233 --> 00:02:14,400
As if my arteries
aren't inflamed enough.

41
00:02:14,433 --> 00:02:15,767
[GROANS]

42
00:02:15,767 --> 00:02:17,833
Morning pass downs are the most
important part of leadership.

43
00:02:17,833 --> 00:02:19,633
It's how you set
the tone for the day.

44
00:02:19,633 --> 00:02:21,467
So yeah, positive vibes only.

45
00:02:21,467 --> 00:02:24,167
Even when everything's on fire.

46
00:02:24,567 --> 00:02:27,300
Good morning, Ward Five!

47
00:02:27,667 --> 00:02:29,167
Millie?

48
00:02:29,167 --> 00:02:30,800
- Coffee.
- Here, boss.

49
00:02:31,267 --> 00:02:32,467
Still at your required temp.

50
00:02:32,467 --> 00:02:33,567
Oh, thank you.

51
00:02:33,567 --> 00:02:35,600
He's annoying. So controlling.

52
00:02:35,600 --> 00:02:37,733
He wants everything
to be his way.

53
00:02:37,733 --> 00:02:40,433
Fix your posture.
You look exhausted.

54
00:02:40,433 --> 00:02:44,567
Nia, it's come to the
hospital's attention that

55
00:02:44,567 --> 00:02:46,867
too many people are
speaking in another language.

56
00:02:46,900 --> 00:02:50,267
Look, he doesn't even
know your name. Geez!

57
00:02:50,267 --> 00:02:51,333
Shh!

58
00:02:52,367 --> 00:02:53,500
[CHUCKLES]

59
00:02:53,500 --> 00:02:54,600
You're new.

60
00:02:54,600 --> 00:02:55,800
I'm your boss.

61
00:02:55,800 --> 00:02:58,167
Try not making me regret that.

62
00:02:58,800 --> 00:03:01,300
Oh, okay. Is Jane--

63
00:03:01,300 --> 00:03:02,633
Oh, no, no. Not available.

64
00:03:02,633 --> 00:03:04,900
You get to deal
with me directly, Nisa.

65
00:03:04,900 --> 00:03:06,233
Noa.

66
00:03:06,233 --> 00:03:07,600
That's what I said.

67
00:03:07,600 --> 00:03:10,467
Oh, this is Millie.
She's the head of HR.

68
00:03:10,900 --> 00:03:12,300
So nice to meet you both.

69
00:03:12,800 --> 00:03:15,167
Announcement, everyone.
Announcement!

70
00:03:15,167 --> 00:03:16,533
[CHUCKLES]

71
00:03:17,200 --> 00:03:19,900
Starting today, you are
only allowed to speak English

72
00:03:19,900 --> 00:03:21,300
while on the premises.

73
00:03:22,800 --> 00:03:25,200
We're in America.

74
00:03:25,600 --> 00:03:27,333
Our patients need
to feel comfortable

75
00:03:27,333 --> 00:03:28,567
with the lingo around here.

76
00:03:28,567 --> 00:03:31,700
(In Spanish) This guy wants me
to stop speaking Spanish?!

77
00:03:31,700 --> 00:03:33,600
He can go to hell!

78
00:03:34,333 --> 00:03:36,533
Anyone caught
breaking the rules

79
00:03:36,533 --> 00:03:38,567
will be subject
to disciplinary action.

80
00:03:39,267 --> 00:03:41,900
Anyone breaking the rules.

81
00:03:44,367 --> 00:03:46,533
Oh, right.

82
00:03:49,633 --> 00:03:50,700
[SNAPS FINGERS]

83
00:03:50,700 --> 00:03:51,733
[SHOE SQUEAKS]

84
00:03:51,733 --> 00:03:52,733
[NOA GRUNTS]

85
00:03:54,533 --> 00:03:55,533
[SIGHS DEEPLY]

86
00:03:55,533 --> 00:03:57,233
So much for positive vibes.

87
00:03:57,567 --> 00:03:58,600
[HUFFS]

88
00:03:58,900 --> 00:04:00,200
Atzin!

89
00:04:00,833 --> 00:04:01,967
Where are you?

90
00:04:11,433 --> 00:04:12,433
[GROANS]

91
00:04:12,433 --> 00:04:13,433
You're not fair!

92
00:04:13,433 --> 00:04:15,600
And your ghost rules
don't make any sense!

93
00:04:15,600 --> 00:04:18,433
Sometimes I can move things.
Sometimes I can't.

94
00:04:18,433 --> 00:04:20,333
What's the deal with that?!

95
00:04:20,767 --> 00:04:24,833
I haven't taken human form
in 30 centuries.

96
00:04:24,833 --> 00:04:26,433
Are you listening to me?

97
00:04:27,733 --> 00:04:29,033
You know what?

98
00:04:29,033 --> 00:04:31,567
Just go to heaven
where you're supposed to go.

99
00:04:31,567 --> 00:04:34,000
And I won't bother her again.
I promise.

100
00:04:34,000 --> 00:04:35,800
Maybe you were white
in your past life, huh?

101
00:04:35,800 --> 00:04:37,300
That's why this is okay for you.

102
00:04:37,300 --> 00:04:38,633
[SNICKERS]

103
00:04:38,633 --> 00:04:40,767
Well, I'm neither. And I'm all.

104
00:04:41,500 --> 00:04:43,667
I'm not attached to any form.

105
00:04:43,967 --> 00:04:45,933
I'm not attached to any race.

106
00:04:45,933 --> 00:04:47,833
But I'm Filipino now.

107
00:04:48,400 --> 00:04:50,600
Fake Filipino!

108
00:04:50,600 --> 00:04:52,967
Irrelevant. Rules are rules.

109
00:04:53,567 --> 00:04:54,533
Watch me.

110
00:04:54,533 --> 00:04:57,833
I'll fix this and
I'll stop this madness.

111
00:05:03,400 --> 00:05:05,000
Oh my god!

112
00:05:05,800 --> 00:05:07,000
Uhm...

113
00:05:07,000 --> 00:05:10,700
Dude, maybe you want to
save some for the rest of us?

114
00:05:10,700 --> 00:05:11,967
Oh my god!

115
00:05:11,967 --> 00:05:13,233
He's one of those idiots

116
00:05:13,233 --> 00:05:15,667
who can eat whatever
they want and not get fat!

117
00:05:15,667 --> 00:05:17,867
[HIGH-PITCHED TONE]

118
00:05:19,833 --> 00:05:21,067
My bad.

119
00:05:21,067 --> 00:05:22,767
I just came to fix the intercom.

120
00:05:28,900 --> 00:05:30,333
[EXHALES]

121
00:05:31,833 --> 00:05:33,767
You people let him die!

122
00:05:33,800 --> 00:05:35,733
He was fine last week!

123
00:05:35,733 --> 00:05:37,933
Ma'am, I understand
your frustration.

124
00:05:37,933 --> 00:05:40,033
- What you have to understand--
- Uhm, Jane! Excuse me!

125
00:05:40,033 --> 00:05:42,033
- Give me one second.
- No! No! No!

126
00:05:42,033 --> 00:05:44,567
We're not done here.
No, I'm not leaving.

127
00:05:44,567 --> 00:05:45,767
- Please, come back here.
- I'm not really leaving.

128
00:05:45,767 --> 00:05:46,867
- I'll be right back.
- Oh my god!

129
00:05:46,867 --> 00:05:48,833
What kind of hospital is this?

130
00:05:48,833 --> 00:05:51,400
You are not here to argue
that stupid language rule.

131
00:05:52,067 --> 00:05:53,467
- No?
- Mh-mm.

132
00:05:53,467 --> 00:05:55,067
I'm not dealing with that today.

133
00:05:55,067 --> 00:05:56,633
...Kind of hospital.

134
00:05:56,633 --> 00:05:58,433
For how long are you
going to keep us waiting here?

135
00:05:58,433 --> 00:06:00,700
- One more second.
- Please come back.

136
00:06:00,700 --> 00:06:01,733
[DOOR CLOSES]

137
00:06:01,733 --> 00:06:03,400
Just go down to Ward One.

138
00:06:03,400 --> 00:06:04,900
They seem to be doing
everything right.

139
00:06:04,900 --> 00:06:07,400
- Okay. Good talk.
- Okay, uhm...

140
00:06:07,400 --> 00:06:09,800
He had a condition for a while.
He just didn't tell his family.

141
00:06:12,367 --> 00:06:13,800
I'm sure he feels
really bad about it.

142
00:06:15,667 --> 00:06:17,467
- How did you know--
- [DOOR OPENS]

143
00:06:17,467 --> 00:06:19,633
Excuse me? For how long
are you going to keep us?

144
00:06:19,633 --> 00:06:22,767
- Please stop blowing us off.
- I have something to tell you.

145
00:06:22,767 --> 00:06:24,333
[DOOR CLOSES]

146
00:06:26,100 --> 00:06:29,633
Infective endocarditis
is a rare but serious infection

147
00:06:29,633 --> 00:06:31,367
of the heart lining and valves.

148
00:06:31,667 --> 00:06:34,600
Usually caused by
Staph aureus or fungi.

149
00:06:35,033 --> 00:06:36,333
And it can kill you?

150
00:06:37,400 --> 00:06:39,400
The bacteria stick
to the endocardium,

151
00:06:39,400 --> 00:06:42,100
form vegetations which lead
to multi-organ failure.

152
00:06:43,600 --> 00:06:45,067
And it can kill you?

153
00:06:46,067 --> 00:06:48,433
Okay, you know what? I'm just
going to read super fast

154
00:06:48,433 --> 00:06:51,000
because you look, like,
really bored right now.

155
00:06:51,000 --> 00:06:53,767
Our management is surgical
incision of the infected valve

156
00:06:53,767 --> 00:06:54,867
with prosthetic replacement.

157
00:06:54,867 --> 00:06:56,033
Which could also kill you.

158
00:06:56,833 --> 00:06:57,833
Yeah.

159
00:06:59,000 --> 00:07:00,033
Do you have any questions?

160
00:07:00,033 --> 00:07:01,800
I just really want to
get the verbiage right

161
00:07:01,800 --> 00:07:03,700
so I don't get written up
or whatever.

162
00:07:03,700 --> 00:07:06,400
Which would also, like, kill me.

163
00:07:06,767 --> 00:07:08,600
Hey lady, do you understand?
What are you trying to say?!

164
00:07:08,600 --> 00:07:10,467
I don't understand
a single word!

165
00:07:10,467 --> 00:07:11,733
Go get a translator!

166
00:07:11,733 --> 00:07:14,633
I don't understand your English,
and you don't understand me.

167
00:07:14,667 --> 00:07:16,667
You just keep talking
and I don't understand

168
00:07:16,667 --> 00:07:18,567
what you're trying to say!

169
00:07:19,000 --> 00:07:21,167
Does your brain work?!

170
00:07:21,767 --> 00:07:23,033
Oh boy.

171
00:07:23,700 --> 00:07:24,633
Don't do it.

172
00:07:24,633 --> 00:07:27,000
The Ward One girls
are evil incarnate.

173
00:07:27,667 --> 00:07:28,700
[SIGHS]

174
00:07:33,567 --> 00:07:34,867
Do you hear that?

175
00:07:35,533 --> 00:07:37,100
I don't hear anything.

176
00:07:37,633 --> 00:07:40,100
Exactly. Zero noise.

177
00:07:40,967 --> 00:07:42,100
No dust.

178
00:07:43,567 --> 00:07:46,600
It even smells like
sampaguitas in here.

179
00:07:48,467 --> 00:07:55,433
["IT'S TOOTSIE"
BY TOOTSIE GUEVARA PLAYING]

180
00:08:10,600 --> 00:08:16,833
["IT'S TOOTSIE" CONTINUES]

181
00:08:16,833 --> 00:08:18,667
Oh, hello!

182
00:08:20,633 --> 00:08:22,167
Oh, my bad.

183
00:08:23,133 --> 00:08:24,867
Ew. I think she's one of them.

184
00:08:24,867 --> 00:08:25,933
Totally.

185
00:08:25,933 --> 00:08:29,167
Oh, Ward Five. So cute.

186
00:08:29,167 --> 00:08:31,700
Can I help you with something?

187
00:08:31,700 --> 00:08:32,767
Um...

188
00:08:32,767 --> 00:08:34,833
Nope. I think I'm good.

189
00:08:34,833 --> 00:08:36,733
Okay, bye!

190
00:08:39,167 --> 00:08:41,167
[TESS]
See? You don't listen.

191
00:08:41,167 --> 00:08:42,567
(In Tagalog)
That stubborn attitude of yours,

192
00:08:42,567 --> 00:08:44,600
you didn't inherit it from me.

193
00:08:47,233 --> 00:08:48,767
(In English) I know, I know.

194
00:08:48,767 --> 00:08:50,833
We're not happy
about the new rule.

195
00:08:50,833 --> 00:08:51,867
[PAPER CRUMPLING]

196
00:08:53,033 --> 00:08:54,833
But I have a surprise
for everyone

197
00:08:54,867 --> 00:08:56,533
that I think will
cheer everyone up.

198
00:08:57,267 --> 00:09:00,600
Here we have a language jar!

199
00:09:00,600 --> 00:09:02,200
Oh, pretty.

200
00:09:02,200 --> 00:09:03,267
What is it?

201
00:09:03,267 --> 00:09:04,933
Let me guess.

202
00:09:04,933 --> 00:09:07,900
If we slip, we have to pay.

203
00:09:07,900 --> 00:09:08,833
Tacky.

204
00:09:08,833 --> 00:09:10,800
It's so I don't have to
write anyone up.

205
00:09:10,800 --> 00:09:13,967
Yay, we can finally go on a
trip to Nickelodeon Studios.

206
00:09:13,967 --> 00:09:17,100
Oh, Ros, that place closed
like 15 years ago.

207
00:09:17,100 --> 00:09:18,233
So did your straight phase?

208
00:09:18,233 --> 00:09:21,900
I told you, those photos
are for fitness inspiration.

209
00:09:21,900 --> 00:09:22,967
[JAR CLINKS]

210
00:09:22,967 --> 00:09:24,100
Atzin, what are you doing?

211
00:09:24,100 --> 00:09:26,067
(In Spanish)
Stupid motherf#$%!

212
00:09:26,067 --> 00:09:27,867
Now I can only speak English,

213
00:09:27,900 --> 00:09:29,133
in a hospital
with these damn patients

214
00:09:29,133 --> 00:09:30,400
from all different countries!

215
00:09:30,400 --> 00:09:33,067
(In English) Wait! Wait, Atzin!
It's only 10 cents a word.

216
00:09:33,067 --> 00:09:34,200
Come back here.

217
00:09:36,067 --> 00:09:37,000
[DOOR SLAMS]

218
00:09:38,233 --> 00:09:40,333
Oh, I get it.

219
00:09:40,333 --> 00:09:42,667
It's like a swear jar.
[CHUCKLES]

220
00:09:47,300 --> 00:09:48,333
[SNICKERS]

221
00:09:48,333 --> 00:09:49,900
Yes!

222
00:09:49,900 --> 00:09:51,733
It'll triple our profits.

223
00:09:51,733 --> 00:09:52,733
Write that down.

224
00:09:52,733 --> 00:09:53,967
Yes, profits.

225
00:09:54,800 --> 00:09:55,867
What are you doing?

226
00:09:55,867 --> 00:09:58,667
(In Tagalog) He'll know
what a real haunting is.

227
00:09:58,667 --> 00:10:00,100
You want to
bully my daughter?

228
00:10:02,200 --> 00:10:03,700
[WIND GUSHING]

229
00:10:03,700 --> 00:10:08,200
- [SCREAMING]
- [ELECTRIC CRACKLE]

230
00:10:09,600 --> 00:10:11,100
[SCREAMING]

231
00:10:11,100 --> 00:10:12,667
(In English)
How do we feel...

232
00:10:12,667 --> 00:10:14,133
[SCREAMING]

233
00:10:14,133 --> 00:10:16,367
...about cutting overtime pay?

234
00:10:16,367 --> 00:10:18,567
Hmm...
Hold on one second.

235
00:10:19,600 --> 00:10:21,300
Ugh, old wiring.

236
00:10:21,300 --> 00:10:23,633
- Call maintenance.
- Anyway...

237
00:10:26,733 --> 00:10:29,033
I'm sorry, I have to
cut my break now.

238
00:10:29,033 --> 00:10:31,367
HIPAA ruins everything.
Gotta go.

239
00:10:31,367 --> 00:10:33,100
Oh, hi, sir.

240
00:10:33,100 --> 00:10:33,900
My name is Camille.

241
00:10:33,900 --> 00:10:36,367
I know I may look
familiar to you.

242
00:10:36,400 --> 00:10:38,033
She used to be
a Pinay celebrity.

243
00:10:38,033 --> 00:10:39,800
And this is Atzin.

244
00:10:39,800 --> 00:10:41,967
I asked them to help because
I really need you to sign off

245
00:10:41,967 --> 00:10:44,167
on the surgery because, like,
the infection could kill you.

246
00:10:44,167 --> 00:10:45,700
(In Dari) Hey girl,
you came last week.

247
00:10:45,700 --> 00:10:47,167
I told you I don’t want
to have the operation.

248
00:10:47,167 --> 00:10:49,233
In the name of God,
please leave me alone.

249
00:10:49,233 --> 00:10:51,333
(In Spanish)
Why are these people idiots?

250
00:10:51,333 --> 00:10:52,933
He’s not even speaking Spanish!
You're wasting my time.

251
00:10:52,933 --> 00:10:54,900
(In English)
Please speak to my wife.

252
00:10:54,900 --> 00:10:55,833
So, it's not Spanish.

253
00:10:55,833 --> 00:10:58,400
- Okay, yeah, I did talk to her.
- Please.

254
00:10:58,400 --> 00:11:01,000
And she said she, like,
didn't want to talk to you

255
00:11:01,000 --> 00:11:02,733
because you're, like,
a bad, corrupt, evil person.

256
00:11:02,733 --> 00:11:04,367
Okay, okay, okay, fine, fine.

257
00:11:04,367 --> 00:11:06,367
I heard it.

258
00:11:06,367 --> 00:11:08,633
Why are you making me
work on my break?

259
00:11:08,667 --> 00:11:10,200
My followers are waiting for me.

260
00:11:10,200 --> 00:11:11,867
Didn't you spend
some time in Dubai?

261
00:11:11,867 --> 00:11:15,167
Yeah, for a movie for
three months in 1991.

262
00:11:15,167 --> 00:11:16,267
I don't understand.

263
00:11:16,267 --> 00:11:18,267
Please, no surgery. Please.

264
00:11:18,267 --> 00:11:19,767
No surgery.

265
00:11:19,767 --> 00:11:22,133
So sorry, sir.
Excuse her.

266
00:11:22,133 --> 00:11:25,700
Her IQ tends to match
the temperature up there.

267
00:11:25,700 --> 00:11:27,267
It's freezing.

268
00:11:28,800 --> 00:11:31,200
But he needs the surgery!
He could die.

269
00:11:32,133 --> 00:11:33,133
Come here.

270
00:11:34,300 --> 00:11:36,133
- [LAUGHTER]
- [COINS CLINK]

271
00:11:36,133 --> 00:11:40,067
(In Bisaya)
She doesn't know how to manage!

272
00:11:40,067 --> 00:11:47,033
[LAUGHING, CHATTERING]

273
00:11:50,967 --> 00:11:53,433
Okay, my turn!
[LAUGHS]

274
00:11:53,433 --> 00:11:55,133
I said my turn!

275
00:11:55,133 --> 00:11:57,367
Sorry.
[CHUCKLES, CLEARS THROAT]

276
00:11:58,700 --> 00:12:04,833
(In Pig Latin)
Noa is actually pretty cool.

277
00:12:04,833 --> 00:12:05,867
(In English)
That's Pig Latin.

278
00:12:05,867 --> 00:12:09,167
[ROS] Yeah, but you have
to say something bad.

279
00:12:09,167 --> 00:12:12,400
Oh, you are a fellow
Pig Latin speaker.

280
00:12:12,400 --> 00:12:15,733
Well, I just, you know,
said that because, um...

281
00:12:15,767 --> 00:12:17,233
You know what, Ros?
I'll give you 10 dollars

282
00:12:17,233 --> 00:12:18,933
if you say a swear word
in Tagalog right now.

283
00:12:18,933 --> 00:12:21,400
[ROSS SCOFFS, LAUGHS]

284
00:12:22,800 --> 00:12:23,800
(In Tagalog)
What the--

285
00:12:23,800 --> 00:12:25,400
[LIGHT SWITCH CLICKING]

286
00:12:25,400 --> 00:12:27,367
[ROS STUTTERING]

287
00:12:28,367 --> 00:12:31,300
(In English) P-Put this away.
It's not even funny.

288
00:12:31,300 --> 00:12:32,800
Come on, everyone.

289
00:12:32,800 --> 00:12:33,800
Back to work.

290
00:12:35,200 --> 00:12:38,267
And that is how
you shut them up.

291
00:12:39,200 --> 00:12:43,467
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

292
00:12:44,833 --> 00:12:47,233
Nora, it's come to our attention

293
00:12:47,233 --> 00:12:49,900
that the nurses on this floor
aren't following the rules.

294
00:12:49,933 --> 00:12:51,367
Boss, I really need your help.

295
00:12:51,367 --> 00:12:54,267
(In Tagalog)
Tell him, "Kiss my ass."

296
00:12:54,267 --> 00:12:55,767
(In English) Guys,
I think we have enough money

297
00:12:55,767 --> 00:12:57,233
to buy Red Ribbon
for the year.

298
00:12:57,233 --> 00:12:58,233
Sir, I assure you,
we're doing every--

299
00:12:58,233 --> 00:13:00,400
(In Tagalog)
It's so dirty!

300
00:13:00,400 --> 00:13:03,433
Tess, don't haunt me, okay?

301
00:13:03,433 --> 00:13:06,333
(In English)
Oh, those are from surgery.

302
00:13:06,333 --> 00:13:08,167
- If he refuses...
- Don't worry.

303
00:13:08,167 --> 00:13:09,933
I brought reinforcements.

304
00:13:09,933 --> 00:13:12,033
Ward One here, everyone.

305
00:13:12,033 --> 00:13:14,067
I heard we're playing
games here today.

306
00:13:14,067 --> 00:13:17,100
I'll gut them like a fish.
[GIGGLES]

307
00:13:17,100 --> 00:13:19,800
- Seriously.
- No, that won't be necessary.

308
00:13:19,800 --> 00:13:22,967
I just need Narnia here to
write up that EVS loudmouth.

309
00:13:23,000 --> 00:13:24,167
Don't worry, everyone.

310
00:13:24,167 --> 00:13:27,200
This isn't some
violent takeover.

311
00:13:27,200 --> 00:13:28,200
[WHISPERS]
Unless you want it to be.

312
00:13:28,200 --> 00:13:29,933
Noa, what are those
delulu-holes doing here?

313
00:13:29,933 --> 00:13:31,033
So, I really need your help.

314
00:13:31,033 --> 00:13:33,133
- I really need your help.
- (In Tagalog) Speak up!

315
00:13:33,133 --> 00:13:35,833
Show him who's boss!
Fight back!

316
00:13:35,833 --> 00:13:37,233
(In English)
Everyone!

317
00:13:37,233 --> 00:13:38,967
Rules are rules!

318
00:13:40,167 --> 00:13:41,933
Ros.

319
00:13:41,933 --> 00:13:43,333
Come with me.

320
00:13:43,333 --> 00:13:45,000
You will be getting a write-up.

321
00:13:46,900 --> 00:13:48,800
Excuse me?

322
00:13:48,800 --> 00:13:51,467
- Never in my 20 years of...
- As Mr. Alderman says,

323
00:13:52,967 --> 00:13:54,400
you will be getting a write-up.

324
00:13:54,400 --> 00:13:56,533
[BUZZING]

325
00:13:57,900 --> 00:13:59,000
[SIGHS SHARPLY]

326
00:14:06,267 --> 00:14:08,967
Tess, Tess, I hope you're proud
of your daughter.

327
00:14:08,967 --> 00:14:11,033
(In Tagalog)
So obedient!

328
00:14:11,033 --> 00:14:12,500
(In English) I'm not.

329
00:14:12,500 --> 00:14:14,100
[KNOCKING]

330
00:14:14,100 --> 00:14:15,267
DonDon, we're busy.

331
00:14:15,267 --> 00:14:17,233
I know, I know, but you
said, like, patients first.

332
00:14:17,233 --> 00:14:19,533
And, oh, no, not another
preventable death.

333
00:14:20,300 --> 00:14:21,400
[GRUNTS]

334
00:14:36,167 --> 00:14:38,233
Why are you going?

335
00:14:38,233 --> 00:14:39,867
Curious.

336
00:14:39,867 --> 00:14:42,167
You know, I think your
daughter is about to quit.

337
00:14:42,167 --> 00:14:44,133
(In Tagalog) You know,
you're becoming human.

338
00:14:44,133 --> 00:14:45,567
You're such a gossip!

339
00:14:47,467 --> 00:14:50,333
(In English) Mr. Hamid, this
procedure will save your life.

340
00:14:50,333 --> 00:14:52,133
(In Dari) I think
I need to rest a little

341
00:14:52,133 --> 00:14:54,867
and not talk
to anyone for a while.

342
00:14:57,967 --> 00:15:00,133
(In Tagalog)
Get rid of him. He's a gossip.

343
00:15:00,133 --> 00:15:02,533
(In English)
Please, I can't focus!

344
00:15:02,567 --> 00:15:03,933
But I didn't say anything.

345
00:15:03,933 --> 00:15:05,933
Or at least, I think I didn't.

346
00:15:05,933 --> 00:15:08,567
I'm, like, literally, totally
holding my breath right now.

347
00:15:08,567 --> 00:15:10,433
Sorry, what is it, Grim?

348
00:15:10,433 --> 00:15:12,600
Oh, I'm sorry.

349
00:15:12,600 --> 00:15:15,567
I just wanted to see if
you needed some help.

350
00:15:15,567 --> 00:15:18,900
Thanks, but I don't think
you speak his language.

351
00:15:18,900 --> 00:15:20,400
Actually, I...

352
00:15:20,400 --> 00:15:22,100
Wait, I totally misjudged you.

353
00:15:22,100 --> 00:15:23,600
I thought you were Filipino.

354
00:15:24,933 --> 00:15:27,200
You know,
maybe we can make a deal.

355
00:15:27,200 --> 00:15:28,333
I'm sorry?

356
00:15:29,067 --> 00:15:30,267
[BREATHES DEEPLY]

357
00:15:30,267 --> 00:15:32,033
Nothing. I just...

358
00:15:32,033 --> 00:15:34,500
don't understand why
everyone's so afraid of death.

359
00:15:35,333 --> 00:15:37,533
Wait, did you just like,
tell him to die?

360
00:15:39,300 --> 00:15:40,567
[SIGHS DEEPLY]

361
00:15:40,567 --> 00:15:42,533
Uh, I'll see myself out.

362
00:15:47,967 --> 00:15:49,100
[WHOOSH SFX]

363
00:15:51,333 --> 00:15:52,933
Such a shame.

364
00:15:52,933 --> 00:15:55,333
Someone felt the need
to report Ward Five.

365
00:15:59,400 --> 00:16:01,300
You! Of course, it was you!

366
00:16:01,300 --> 00:16:03,200
- [GRIM GROANING]
- [GASPS]

367
00:16:03,200 --> 00:16:05,700
Finally, I figured it out.

368
00:16:05,700 --> 00:16:09,000
My mood swings are useful
for something.

369
00:16:09,033 --> 00:16:10,733
- [CHUCKLES]
- That hurt!

370
00:16:10,733 --> 00:16:12,333
I know, you're right.

371
00:16:12,333 --> 00:16:14,433
You can make her life
a living hell.

372
00:16:14,433 --> 00:16:15,967
Are you proud of yourself?

373
00:16:18,567 --> 00:16:21,367
Why? Do you think she can
do this forever?

374
00:16:21,567 --> 00:16:25,333
She's in a ward, full of ghosts,
full of sick people.

375
00:16:25,533 --> 00:16:27,533
Her plate's already full, right?

376
00:16:27,967 --> 00:16:28,967
[GRIM SCOFFS]

377
00:16:28,967 --> 00:16:30,300
I feel sorry for her.

378
00:16:31,000 --> 00:16:33,433
I wanted to help her patient,

379
00:16:33,433 --> 00:16:36,000
but I don't feel
like it anymore.

380
00:16:37,633 --> 00:16:38,600
Fine!

381
00:16:39,167 --> 00:16:40,300
[TESS] Help her.

382
00:16:41,400 --> 00:16:45,200
And I promise,
I will cross over.

383
00:16:54,333 --> 00:16:56,067
[GRIM EXHALES SHARPLY]

384
00:16:56,067 --> 00:16:59,767
It's been a couple of centuries
since I spoke his language.

385
00:16:59,767 --> 00:17:03,133
Why do we have to
be funny all the time?

386
00:17:03,133 --> 00:17:07,233
Sorry, I meant couple of years
since I spoke Dari.

387
00:17:07,233 --> 00:17:08,600
I can help explain.

388
00:17:10,167 --> 00:17:11,367
(In Arabic) Peace be upon you.

389
00:17:11,367 --> 00:17:13,133
(In Arabic) And upon you
be peace.

390
00:17:16,100 --> 00:17:18,233
(In Dari) Look into
my eyes, Mr. Hamid.

391
00:17:18,800 --> 00:17:21,333
Hell is no joke.

392
00:17:21,767 --> 00:17:25,300
If you die now,
do you know where you’ll go?

393
00:17:27,233 --> 00:17:29,100
Okay, okay, I'll do the surgery!

394
00:17:29,100 --> 00:17:30,367
[HAMID] I'll do the surgery.

395
00:17:30,367 --> 00:17:32,733
You ate that!
That was like so hot.

396
00:17:32,733 --> 00:17:34,567
Wow, thank you.

397
00:17:34,567 --> 00:17:35,700
That was...

398
00:17:40,667 --> 00:17:41,767
Excuse me.

399
00:17:50,833 --> 00:17:52,400
What are you thinking, dear?

400
00:17:59,800 --> 00:18:04,533
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

401
00:18:04,533 --> 00:18:05,667
[NOA] I got it, Mom.

402
00:18:13,700 --> 00:18:14,700
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

403
00:18:19,267 --> 00:18:21,633
Mr. Alderman, this stops now.

404
00:18:21,867 --> 00:18:23,600
Excuse me?

405
00:18:23,600 --> 00:18:25,367
I used to think speaking
perfect English

406
00:18:25,367 --> 00:18:26,433
meant that you were smart.

407
00:18:26,433 --> 00:18:28,333
But today, a man chose death

408
00:18:28,333 --> 00:18:30,133
because he couldn't
understand us!

409
00:18:30,133 --> 00:18:31,500
Rules are rules.

410
00:18:31,700 --> 00:18:34,200
That rule, Mr. Alderman,
is not ethical.

411
00:18:34,200 --> 00:18:36,300
People don't come
in one language.

412
00:18:36,300 --> 00:18:38,500
And we speak these languages
because our patients do.

413
00:18:38,500 --> 00:18:40,467
Because their families do.

414
00:18:41,233 --> 00:18:43,400
Because our moms do.

415
00:18:43,400 --> 00:18:44,767
And we can't erase that.

416
00:18:44,767 --> 00:18:46,533
Not now. Not ever!

417
00:18:46,533 --> 00:18:48,200
I'm with Noa on this.

418
00:18:48,400 --> 00:18:51,233
It doesn't matter what you speak
as long as you're a good person.

419
00:18:51,433 --> 00:18:54,533
Wait, you speak English?
Since when?

420
00:18:57,533 --> 00:18:58,700
Ugh.

421
00:18:59,767 --> 00:19:01,100
Millie!

422
00:19:01,533 --> 00:19:02,667
Coming!

423
00:19:05,167 --> 00:19:07,167
[SLOW CLAP]

424
00:19:07,167 --> 00:19:14,100
[APPLAUSE]

425
00:19:14,800 --> 00:19:21,800
[CHEERING]

426
00:19:21,800 --> 00:19:28,700
[GENTLE MUSIC PLAYING]

427
00:19:35,867 --> 00:19:37,467
[NOA SIGHS]

428
00:19:37,467 --> 00:19:38,700
[PAPER RIPPING]

429
00:19:41,767 --> 00:19:44,367
You certainly put on
a show today.

430
00:19:44,567 --> 00:19:45,767
[NOA] Oh, no.

431
00:19:46,200 --> 00:19:47,567
Took me a minute.

432
00:19:47,567 --> 00:19:50,733
But I had legal go through
all those damn rules.

433
00:19:51,200 --> 00:19:52,767
Turns out, they can't tell us

434
00:19:52,767 --> 00:19:56,767
they can't tell us what language
we can speak inside these walls.

435
00:19:57,400 --> 00:19:58,767
So, I'm not fired?

436
00:19:58,767 --> 00:20:00,867
Nope. Not yet.

437
00:20:01,500 --> 00:20:04,433
But that doesn't mean you didn't
put a target on your back.

438
00:20:08,633 --> 00:20:11,467
It's a good thing you
have me protecting it.

439
00:20:19,767 --> 00:20:26,767
[GENTLE MUSIC PLAYING]

440
00:20:38,833 --> 00:20:42,900
You people keep clutching
at air like it'll hold you back.

441
00:20:43,933 --> 00:20:46,300
Oh, come on, please. Admit it.

442
00:20:46,300 --> 00:20:48,467
You can see the goodness
in her heart.

443
00:20:48,467 --> 00:20:51,433
That's why you can't stop
yourself from helping her.

444
00:20:51,900 --> 00:20:53,467
She got it from her mom.

445
00:20:55,767 --> 00:20:56,900
[GRIM CHUCKLES]

446
00:20:58,533 --> 00:20:59,667
Are you ready?

447
00:21:00,733 --> 00:21:01,867
Ready for what?

448
00:21:02,733 --> 00:21:04,233
Huh?

449
00:21:04,533 --> 00:21:07,667
Didn't you say that if
I helped her, you'd move on?

450
00:21:07,867 --> 00:21:11,767
I didn't say when.
So, technically, I didn't lie.

451
00:21:11,800 --> 00:21:13,900
Okay, so you really want
to level up this game?

452
00:21:13,900 --> 00:21:15,667
Okay, fine-- Hey!

453
00:21:17,700 --> 00:21:18,867
Thought so.

454
00:21:19,600 --> 00:21:21,733
You do realize that
I have a scythe right?

455
00:21:24,800 --> 00:21:31,767
[MELLOW MUSIC PLAYING]

456
00:21:46,800 --> 00:21:53,767
[MELLOW MUSIC CONTINUES]

457
00:22:08,833 --> 00:22:15,733
[MELLOW MUSIC CONTINUES]

458
00:22:30,833 --> 00:22:37,767
[MELLOW MUSIC CONTINUES]

459
00:22:52,867 --> 00:22:59,767
[MELLOW MUSIC CONTINUES]

460
00:23:14,833 --> 00:23:21,800
[MELLOW MUSIC CONTINUES]

